article.description: Nate Kratch scored 17 points on 6-of-8 shooting and Jared Brownridge made 5 of 7 shots and scored 12 to help Santa Clara beat San Diego 65-53 Saturday night.
article.headline: Kratch, Brownridge lead Santa Clara past San Diego 65-53
article.linkText: Kratch, Brownridge lead Santa Clara past San Diego 65-53
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Nate Kratch scored 17 points on 6-of-8 shooting and Jared Brownridge made 5 of 7 shots and scored 12 to help Santa Clara beat San Diego 65-53 Saturday night. Kai Healey and KJ Feagin scored 11 apiece for Santa Clara (6-12, 2-4 West Coast Conference). Healy made a career-high three 3-pointers. Healey and Matt Hauser scored five points each during a 14-2 run that gave the Broncos a 50-36 lead with nine minutes to play. A 3-point play by Brett Bailey pulled the Toreros within eight with 50 seconds left, but Kratch and Feagin combined to make 4 of 4 free throws from there to seal it. Bailey led San Diego (5-10, 0-4) with a career-high 22 points, on 9-of-16 shooting, and eight rebounds. Santa Clara made 23 of 45 (51 percent) field goal attempts while limiting San Diego to 38 percent (21-of-56) shooting.
